content:
Estimated Examples:
Example 1:
Text: Nothing messed up from where I'm sitting. What kind of messed up?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 2:
Text: Molte grazie, just one last thing, if this is the only source then how I'm supposed to cite it there. Do you have any better way?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 3:
Text: The block has indeed expired.  What message are you getting when you try to edit?
Annotation from annotator: 9

Example 4:
Text: Jenny and Silas info should surface within the week, Daily Mail will have some reception for him and her. "India's murder" and "Fued with Lynsey Nolan" maybe?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Example 5:
Text: Hi there. On a tangential note, would you happen to be <person>?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 6:
Text: I looked at all the provinces and regencies listed on <url> - so that trick is mostly played out. I'm going down the alphabet now and I'm at the R's - if you want to work, maybe you could start at the end of the alphabet so we don't interfere with each other, meet in the middle?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 7:
Text: I forgot to add, above, that Jed's site also hosts some anti-CF papers.  So, if ALL the papers there are garbage, those would be, too, right?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 8:
Text: hahah, thanks! Must admit, when I saw the title of this section I was thinking "oh lord, another what-is-the-wiki-coming-to comment.." :p. How goes?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 9:
Text: Again, why are you simply reverting wholesale and without any explanation? Would you rather the article be out of line with the policies and guidelines, among other problems?
Annotation from annotator: 3

Example 10:
Text: I was thinking on it, but one question: I see several articles either deleted or promoted to FA after the oldid the sweeps uses. I'm assuming we simply ignore these?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 11:
Text: Unless im making a major mistake here, this article was about a Not for profit organisation which seemed notable enough to give the origional creator at least some time to source it. Are you sure this had to be a speedy?
Annotation from annotator: 6

Example 12:
Text: Also, i'd like to know what you think of William Harris. Is he affiliated with the Discovery Institute?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Example 13:
Text: Hmm, I'm not sure...maybe you need to clear your cache? Or did you create the new username first, before asking me to change your old one?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 14:
Text: Currently, <url> is a subcategory of <url>. What would you suggest doing about this?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 15:
Text: I just wanted to mention, I haven't been on VIA since I was 12 or so, and I've never taken a Greyhound bus to or from London...but I don't recall there being overwhelming complaints about VIA.  I mean, there is general complaining, like there always is about any transportation system...isn't it faster than the bus though, even if it is more expensive?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 16:
Text: Acad, I see we have one fairly ambiguous comment at <url>, dealing with hyphenation, which is one of the things we agree on, if memory serves.  Any advance on 4 people who care?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 17:
Text: Who is going to contact all of the users?  Is a bot being set to do that in the event it's necessary, or is it being done manually?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 18:
Text: I seeu2014yes, those can easily be changed back. Would you rather I start a fresh discussion about these?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 19:
Text: You speedy-delete-tagged <url> and <url> as <nowiki><person></nowiki>. What maintenance work were you weanting to do with them?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 20:
Text: Ah okay. In that case I'm going to tag it for deletion as a redundant redirect, if that's okay with you?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 21:
Text: I guess I must have misunderstood, sorry for that. Exactly what do you mean by having my promise to not use the tools for a year enforced by a bureaucrat?
Annotation from annotator: 17

Example 22:
Text: I'm also a bit weary of this discussion, and I'm afraid the central argument stands. But perhaps if you wish to continue it, you'd do a bit of the searching, and report your results?
Annotation from annotator: 7

Example 23:
Text: Why did you remove the pollution references on <url>. Do you have a source which refutes this claim?
Annotation from annotator: 4

Example 24:
Text: I would like to nominate you for adminship.  Would you accept now?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 25:
Text: Have you as yet cast your own vote for <url>? Is there anything you can do to address some of the questions?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Example 26:
Text: Stephen's solution certainly isn't optimal. Fancy giving me a basic rundown on the problem here and I'll see if I can devise a more elegant one?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 27:
Text: Just noticed that the "time" field is eliminated from the collapsable boxes. Could you make this something that is displayed when the box is expanded?
Annotation from annotator: 10

Example 28:
Text: Is your username Davshul? When would you be online?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 29:
Text: Say what? And what does this have to do with "Happy New Year" and my pretty picture?
Annotation from annotator: 5

Example 30:
Text: Are you kidding me? Do you even bother to click on <url> to see its fleet?
Annotation from annotator: 1

Target Example:
Text: Thanks a lot for clearing that up. Do you also happen to know about the age of consent in Thailand, and why he could be charge with child sex offenses even though she was 17 years old?
Annotation from annotator:
